-- China to Crack Down on Counterfeit Goods, Pirated Software, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-19T17:34:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/china-to-start-national-campaign-against-counterfeit-goods-xinhua-reports.html
China will start a new national
campaign against counterfeited and pirated goods at both the
production and distribution levels, Xinhua News Agency said,
citing a State Council meeeting at which Premier Wen Jiabao
presided.  The half-year campaign, to start at the end of the month,
will focus on pirated publications, software, DVDs and designs,
as well as violations of trademarks and patents, and on the
import and export of fake goods, Xinhua said.  Government agencies have been ordered to use only
authorized software and updates, the news agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  